{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "0f5a5a7b-46b7-4b84-a0ee-6c08e2f6a3da",
    "name": "Zamin — Real Estate Listings API",
    "description": "# Zamin API collection\n\nImport this file into Postman, start the API, then send **Auth / Login as Admin** and **Auth / Login as Editor**. The login requests save access and refresh tokens automatically.\n\n## Local demo setup\n\n1. Run `python3 seed.py` and start the API at `http://127.0.0.1:8000`.\n2. Copy the passwords from the ignored local `credentials.txt` file into the `adminPassword` and `editorPassword` collection variables. Passwords are deliberately not stored in this collection.\n3. Send **Public / List Public Cities** once; it selects Lahore (or the first active city) for `cityId`.\n\nThe collection includes safe examples and state-changing requests. Requests that create, update, approve, reject, deactivate, or delete data are clearly named. Image-upload requests require selecting a local JPEG, PNG, or WEBP file in Postman.\n\nThe **Admin via Editor Listing APIs** folder proves that an admin token can use every `/api/v1/editor/listings` operation and manage listings from every editor.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
